
About
=====


Often times we want to run GROMACS analysis tools on data from Python scripts.
It can be tiresome to handle this ourselves, so this is a simple library of functions wrapping commonly used utilities.


Dependencies
============

  Python 2.7    : http://python.org
  GROMACS       : http://www.gromacs.org
  Numpy         : http://numpy.scipy.org
  ezlog         : https://github.com/badi/ezlog


Example
=======

from gmx import g_rms

output = '/dev/null'
rmsd = g_rms(stdout=output, stderr=output)
results = rmsd(s='tests/test.pdb', f='tests/test.xtc', n='tests/test.ndx', o='rmsd.xvg')

for frame, value in enumerate(results):
    print frame, value
